"The ministry sadly announces the first death of a COVID-19 patient, who was admitted to treatment facility on April 13," Nkosi said. The 59-year-old man was diagnosed on admission with pneumonia, with diabetes as an underlying condition. He died on Wednesday after his condition suddenly worsened. Eswatini, widely known as Swaziland, has so far recorded 17 cases of infection.  --NEWS24-- 